What is PHP
PHP is an acronym for "PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor"
PHP is a server-side scripting language to develop interactive and dynamic web applications
PHP is a loosely type language
PHP is a widely-used, open-source language
Extension of PHP file is .php
Points to Remember:
PHP is a case sensitive language
Each statement ends with a semicolon (;)
Each keyword starting from small letter
Support single line or multiline comments
// single line comments
/*
Multi line comments
*/
The dot(.) operator is used to concatenate the strings.


PHP Syntax:
<?php
// PHP code 
?>
